The paper deals with the topological concept of transversality and its stability under perturbations, which is a topic in computational geometry (cs.CG). The use of persistent homology suggests a connection to computational topology and data analysis (cs.DS, cs.SI). The applications to fixed points and contours of mappings suggest a connection to numerical analysis (cs.NA) and game theory (cs.GT), respectively.
